# Project 1 — PGPSLAW
# Legal Sector Cloud Identity & Security Transformation

## Project Overview
PGPSLAW required a complete modernization of their identity infrastructure, endpoint management, security posture, and collaboration environment. The organization operated with legacy on-premises Active Directory infrastructure, inconsistent user access management, decentralized file storage, and minimal device compliance enforcement.

The objective was to migrate the organization into a modern Microsoft cloud-first architecture using:

- Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)
- Microsoft Intune
- Conditional Access
- SharePoint Online
- RBAC Security Architecture
- Microsoft Defender Integration
- Hybrid Identity Synchronization
- MFA Enforcement
- Zero Trust Security Principles

This project focused heavily on legal-sector compliance, document confidentiality, secure remote work enablement, and least-privilege administrative design.

